{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17616616","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17616616"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:05:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:05:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16408"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16408","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16408"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0,0.05,0.11,0.79]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9099"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72926"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9099","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9099"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16408"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58396"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4838"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10354"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21607"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21612"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72926","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72926"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 89-year-old patient was electively admitted for a right hemicolectomy. He is functionally independent and lives at home alone. On postop day 2, he was found at 2am wandering into another patient\u0027s room. He was disorientated to time, place and person.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most accurate statement regarding delirium?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Delirium is a chronic confusional state","Delirium typically develops over several weeks","Delirium has a consistent level of consciousness","Delirium primarily affects long-term memory","Delirium disrupts the sleep-wake cycle"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis case presents a typical example of delirium, characterised by acute onset confusion, fluctuating consciousness, and inattention. Understanding the key features of delirium is crucial for accurate diagnosis and management.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelirium disrupts the sleep-wake cycle\u003C/strong\u003E. Disturbance of the sleep-wake cycle is a cardinal feature of delirium, with patients often experiencing daytime drowsiness and nighttime agitation. This disruption is thought to be related to dysfunction of circadian rhythm regulation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelirium is a chronic confusional state\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Delirium is an acute condition with rapid onset (usually hours to days). This acute onset helps distinguish it from chronic cognitive conditions such as dementia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelirium typically develops over several weeks\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. The onset of delirium is typically acute, developing over hours to days, not weeks. This rapid onset is a key diagnostic feature.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelirium has a consistent level of consciousness\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Fluctuation in consciousness and attention is a defining characteristic of delirium. Patients may appear lucid at times and confused at others within the same day.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelirium primarily affects long-term memory\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. While memory can be affected in delirium, the primary cognitive disturbance is in attention and consciousness. Long-term memory impairment is more characteristic of dementia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe highest rates of delirium are found in older patients in the surgical, palliative care and intensive care settings.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Delirium is an acute confusional state characterised by fluctuating consciousness, inattention, and disorganised thinking.","Key features of delirium include disturbance of sleep-wake cycle, perceptual disturbances, and an acute onset.","Delirium is distinguished from dementia by its acute onset and potentially reversible nature."],"references":["Pisani MA, D\u0027Ambrosio C. Sleep and Delirium in Adults Who Are Critically Ill: A Contemporary Review. Chest. 2020 Apr;157(4):977-984. doi: 10.1016/j.chest.2019.12.003. Epub 2019 Dec 23. PMID: 31874132.","Wilson JE, Mart MF, Cunningham C, Shehabi Y, Girard TD, MacLullich AMJ, Slooter AJC, Ely EW. Delirium. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2020 Nov 12;6(1):90. doi: 10.1038/s41572-020-00223-4. Erratum in: Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2020 Dec 1;6(1):94. doi: 10.1038/s41572-020-00236-z. PMID: 33184265; PMCID: PMC9012267.","Wilson JE, Mart MF, Cunningham C, Shehabi Y, Girard TD, MacLullich AMJ, Slooter AJC, Ely EW. Delirium. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2020 Nov 12;6(1):90. doi: 10.1038/s41572-020-00223-4. Erratum in: Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2020 Dec 1;6(1):94. doi: 10.1038/s41572-020-00236-z. PMID: 33184265; PMCID: PMC9012267."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58396"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16408"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58396","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58396"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-22T18:29:57+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T15:25:32+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9099"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72926"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"6","links":{